-- Ohio State Defeats No. 1 Seed Syracuse 77-70 in NCAA Tournament
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-03-25T01:32:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-25/ohio-state-defeats-no-1-seed-syracuse-77-70-in-ncaa-tournament.html
Second-seeded  Ohio State University 
eliminated No. 1 seed Syracuse University 77-70 in the East
Region’s final of the national men’s college basketball
championship.  Jared Sullinger had 19 points for Ohio State and Lenzelle
Smith Jr. added 18 points at TD Garden in  Boston .  Syracuse’s loss leaves top seeds Kentucky and  Kansas  in the
competition.  The Buckeyes advance to the semifinals of the National
Collegiate Athletic Association championship on March 31 where
they will play  North Carolina  or Kansas.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nancy Kercheval at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net  